description:
...just remember, the storm doesn’t last forever. 
It can scare you; it can shake you to your core. 
But it never lasts. 
The rain subsided and the thunder dies, and the winds calm to a soft whisper. 
And that moment after the storm clouds pass, when all is silent and still, you find peace. 
Quiet, gentle peace. ~S.L. Jennings
